You can just use `gapi.auth2.getAuthInstance().signIn()` to sign in and then use the Google ID token from that library to sign in to Firebase Auth.

This is documented in [Firebase Official docs](https://firebase.google.com/docs/auth/web/google-signin#advanced:-handle-the-sign-in-flow-manually).

    // Build Firebase credential with the Google ID token.
    const credential = firebase.auth.GoogleAuthProvider.credential(
        googleUser.getAuthResponse().id_token);
    // Sign in with credential from the Google user silently.
    firebase.auth().signInWithCredential(credential)
      .then((result) =&gt; {
        // User signed in.
      })
      .catch((error) =&gt; {
        // Error occurred.
      });

